\f3\b \cf0 NNM-mapper.amxd
\f2\b0 \
Receives list of parameters from input devices (using Max send/receive) or from OSC, and controls the parameters of any other target device in the Live set.\
Different mapping algorithms are available:\
- Regression with a Multi-Layer Perceptron\
- Regression with K-Nearest Neighbours\
- Inverse Distance Weighted Interpolation\
\
\
\
\

\f3\b Send and receive lists between devices
\f2\b0 \
Input devices send lists of parameters (can be any length) to NNM-mapper using Max send / receive.\
Each Input devices has a default send name, that can be changed to anything.\
\
One special case : when a send / receive name contains \'ab\'a0track#\'a0\'bb : \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 track# is replaced by current track # (starts from 1)\
So input devices and NNM-mappers can be grouped and saved as instrument / effect Rack presets, and then placed or duplicated to other tracks, preserving send / receive associations.\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \ul \ulc0 NNM_input_devices\ulnone \
All these devices are Max Audio Effects, so they can be used in any track (Audio or MIDI)\
(1 exception : NNM.LeapMotion.makeNote = Max MIDI Effect)\
\
